@paimon.overview.description: A lake format that enables building a Realtime Lakehouse Architecture with Flink and Spark for both streaming and batch operations. Innovatively combines lake format and LSM structure, bringing realtime streaming updates into the lake architecture.
Apache Paimon is developed by an open an: Apache Paimon is developed by an open and friendly community. Everybody is cordially welcome to join the community and contribute to Apache Paimon.
Append table (no primary-key) provides l: Append table (no primary-key) provides large scale batch and streaming processing capability. Supports compaction with z-order sorting.
Based on indexes such as minmax, filter: Based on indexes such as minmax, filter irrelevant files and provide high-performance queries, more indexes are being supported.
Defining Merge Engines, update records h: Defining Merge Engines, update records however you like. Deduplicate to keep last row, or partial-update, or aggregate records, or first-row, you decide.
Defining changelog-producer, produce cor: Defining changelog-producer, produce correct and complete changelog in updates for merge engines, simplifying your streaming analytics.
Low cost, High reliability, Scalable met: Low cost, High reliability, Scalable metadata, Time Travel and Full Schema Evolution. All advantage as a data lake storage.
One Storage for All Your Data: One Storage for All Your Data
Primary-key table supports real-time str: Primary-key table supports real-time streaming updates of large amounts of data. Real-time query within 1 minute.
Various companies and organizations are: Various companies and organizations are using Paimon for production and commercial products.
